name: Daviess County Public Library
directions:
First floor - Enter building and turn right at help desk. Follow wall to gendered bathrooms.
Second floor - Enter building and take either set of stairs up. Turn right at the help desk and follow the wall past teen section to gendered bathrooms.
comment: Free for everyone! DCPL is very supportive, and encourages all patrons to use the bathroom they are most comfortable in.

name: Holiday World & Splashin' Safari
directions:
Neutral/Family bathrooms: Splashin' Safari, Christmas, First Aid.
Single-stall gendered: Inside Plymouth Rock Café in Thanksgiving.
Gendered large bathrooms: Splashin' Safari, Halloween, 4th of July, Christmas, Thanksgiving.
First-aid (tall, red-roofed building in the center of the park) also has an "overstimulation room" designated for neurodivergent Guests and employees to use as needed.
comment: Must be a Guest or employee to enter. Holiday World & Splashin' Safari actively encourages Guests and employees to use whichever bathroom that they are most comfortable with.

They are a queer venue and advertise the loos as public bathrooms for anyone to use. There are many single cubicles all of which are gender neutral, some have sinks inside them and some don't. They have accessible loos and baby changing also.
Free sanitary producta are also available.
